JOINS:- Joins are used to retrieve data from  multiple tables. 
 EQUI JOIN:-Based on equality operator we are retrieving data from multiple tables.
========== Here joining conditional columns must belongs to same datatype.

8i joins or NON ANSI joins syntax:-
=================================
select col1,col2.......
from tablename1 , tablename2
where tablename1.commoncolumnname= tablename2.Commoncolumnname;
      --------------------------------------------------------
                                 ||
                                 ||
                          (join condition)

9i joins or ANSI JOINS syntax:-
==============================
Syntax:-
========
select col1,col2.......
from tablename1 join tablename2
on tablename1.commoncolumnname= tablename2.Commoncolumnname;
   --------------------------------------------------------
                               ||
                               ||
                         (join condition)

============================
ANSI
-------------
SQL> SELECT e.ename, d.dname FROM emp e JOIN dept d ON e.deptno = d.deptno;

